This is a blog written in Python using Django web framework. I am new to Django, so this app is used to help me learn Django. It is really an excellent web framework. Feel free to use this blog!

I have deployed this blog app at dotcloud, please refer dotcloud docs http://docs.dotcloud.com/tutorials/django

Usage:
Make sure you have Django installed(Mine is Django 1.3). In this app Django use tagging and markdown tools, so you have to install tagging and markdown component. Google (python tagging) & (python markdown).

1. git clone git@github.com/JasonSun/Jason-Blog.git Your_Blog
2. do some updates in setting.py file
3. python manage.py runserver
4. open your browser, type 'localhost:8000'

Thanks very much for Mark's contribution of his blog. Please refer to:
Source code: https://github.com/mliu7/personal-django-blog
Mark's Blog: http://markliu.me

